org.lwjgl.examples.spaceinvaders

Class Entity

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.lwjgl.examples.spaceinvaders.Entity
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AlienEntity, ShipEntity, ShotEntity

    public abstract class Entity
extends java.lang.Object
    An entity represents any element that appears in the game. The entity is responsible for resolving collisions and movement based on a set of properties defined either by subclass or externally. Note that doubles are used for positions. This may seem strange given that pixels locations are integers. However, using double means that an entity can move a partial pixel. It doesn't of course mean that they will be display half way through a pixel but allows us not lose accuracy as we move.
